The paper deals with the robustness of complex networks, which is a topic that can be approached from different perspectives in computer science. The proposed solution involves the use of Principal Component Analysis (PCA), which is a technique commonly used in machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed method to different types of networks, such as social networks, transportation networks, and power grids, which are relevant to the sub-categories of network science (cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS). Finally, the paper addresses the issue of comparing the robustness of different networks, which is related to the field of control and systems engineering (cs.SY).
